{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships"}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure","platforms":[{"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"15.0"},{"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"13.0"},{"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"16.0"},{"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0"},{"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"11.0"}],"modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents29OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminateV"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudscheckboxitemindeterminate"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Checkbox is a UI element that allows to select multiple options from a set of mutually non exclusive choices."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Checkbox item covers a wider range of contexts by allowing to toggle the visibility of additional text labels and icon assets."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"text":"Layouts","type":"heading","anchor":"Layouts","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"text":": the component has a leading indicator, a label and optional helper texts, and an optional trailing decorative icon","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"inverse"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": like the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" layout but with a trailing checkbox indicator and a leading optional image","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Indicator-states","text":"Indicator states","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The checkbox indicator has three available states:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"selected"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": the checkbox is filled with a tick, the user has made the action to select the checkbox","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"unselected","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": the checkbox is empty, does not contain a tick, the user has made the action to unselect or did not select yet the checkbox"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"indeterminate","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": mike a prefilled or preticked checkbox, the user did not do anything on it yet","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need a checkbox with only two states to manage use instead ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Particular-cases","level":2,"text":"Particular cases"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate"},{"type":"text","text":" can be related to an error situation, for example troubles for a formular."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A dedicated look and feel is implemented for that if the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isError"},{"type":"text","text":" flag is risen."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In that case if the component displayed an icon, this icon will be replaced automatically by an error icon."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition, the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate"},{"type":"text","text":" can be in read only mode, i.e. the user cannot interact with the component yet"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but this component must not be considered as disabled."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component does not follow the right-to-left (RTL) \/ left-to-right (LTR) mode returned by the system as it could have some meaning"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to have for example the indicator in trailing position for LTR mode and vice versa."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, if the component has an icon in leading position (RTL mode) or in trailing position (LTR), the content of the icon is never changed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It could lead to a loss of meaning or semantics in the icon. Thus a specific flag can be used to flip the icon content whatever the layout direction is."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It prevents the user do implement its own rules to flip or not image."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Accessibility considerations","level":2,"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Voice Over"}]},{"type":"text","text":" will use several elements to describe the component: if component disabled \/ read only, if error context, the label and helper texts and a custom checkbox trait."}]},{"text":"Forbidden by design","type":"heading","anchor":"Forbidden-by-design","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a read only component.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component."}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both a read only and a disabled component."}]}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples","type":"heading"},{"code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have an indeterminate state checkbox","    @Published var selection: OUDSCheckboxIndicatorState = .indeterminate","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(selection: $selection, label: \"Hello world\")","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but in read only mode (user cannot interact yet, but not disabled).","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(selection: $selection, label: \"Hello world\", isReadOnly: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label and a description as helper text.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(selection: $selection, label: \"Bazinga!\", description: \"Doll-Dagga Buzz-Buzz Ziggety-Zag\")","","    \/\/ A trailing checkbox with a label, an helper text and an icon.","    \/\/ The reversed layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(selection: $selection,","                                  label: \"We live in a fabled world\",","                                  description: \"Of dreaming boys and wide-eyed girls\",","                                  isReversed: true,","                                  icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"))","","    \/\/ If on error, add an error message can help user to understand error context","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(selection: $selection,","                                  label: \"We live in a fabled world\",","                                  isError: true,","                                  errorText: \"Something wrong\",","                                  hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but disabled.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(selection: $selection, label: \"Hello world\")","        .disabled(true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label and and icon but with the icon flipped vertically","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(isOn: $selection,","                                  label: \"Cocorico !\",","                                  icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","                                  flipIcon: true)","","    \/\/ Never disable a read only or an error-related checkbox as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(selection: $selection, label: \"Hello world\", isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(selection: $selection, label: \"Hello world\", isReadyOnly: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want to manage the RTL mode quite easily and switch your layouts (flip image, indicator in RTL leading i.e. in the right):"}]},{"code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(isOn: $selection,","                                  label: \"Cocorico !\",","                                  icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","                                  flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft,","                                  isInversed: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Suggestions","level":2,"anchor":"Suggestions"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"According to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-checkbox"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the checkbox by default must be used in unselected state.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","text":"Design documentation","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"unified-design-system.orange.com","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"unified-design-system.orange.com"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-checkbox","type":"reference"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Themes rendering","level":2,"anchor":"Themes-rendering"},{"type":"heading","text":"Orange","level":3,"anchor":"Orange"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Orange","type":"image"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Orange Compact","level":3,"anchor":"Orange-Compact"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_chec